    {
      "id": "0fedc67c12d28c0d2cc6aa9ee7d7c823d05065b2",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-11-19 08:02:00.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nGiven that LFSCK phase 2 is planned to land for 2.6, which will replace the old e2fsprogs-based lfsck, I think it makes sense to only land this for b2_5 and b2_4.  The setea functionality was an acceptable hack for lfsck when it was necessary, but I don't want to add it back if we no longer need it.\n\nDoes this patch apply cleanly to those older branches?  If yes, then Oleg should cherry-pick there. If not, then this patch should be rebased and submitted to the branch(es).",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
